Doc. PhDr. '''František Kopečný''', DrSc. (born 4 October 1909 in [[Určice]] – died 27 March 1990 in [[Vrahovice]]) was Czech [[Czech studies|bohemist]] and [[Slavistics|slavist]]. He was interested in [[etymology]] and [[dialectology]].
He studied [[Czech language|Czech]] and German languages at the [[Masaryk University]]. He then worked at the [[Palacký University]]. With colleagues, he wrote an [[Old Church Slavonic|Old Slavic]] dictionary. From 1952, he worked at [[Czechoslovak Academy of Sciences]], where he wrote an [[Etymological dictionary]] (Czech: ''Etymologický slovník'').<ref>{{cite web | url = http://old.ujc.avcr.cz/lingviste/kopecny-frantisek.html | title = František Kopečný | last = | first = | date = | website = Institute of the Czech Language of the Czech Academy of Sciences | publisher = | access-date = 3 March 2017 | quote = }}</ref>
