{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2018}} {{Use Indian English|date=October 2018}} {{Infobox person | name = Garima Sanjay | image = [[File:Author Garima Sanjay.jpg|Author Garima Sanjay|200px]] | alt = | caption = Garima Sanjay | nationality = [[Indian people|Indian]] | occupation = [[Author]] | birth_place = [[Allahabad]] [[Uttar Pradesh]] [[India]] | spouse = Sanjay Kumar | children = Shatrrundam Srivastav | relatives = |alma_mater = [[Allahabad University]] | website = }} '''Garima Sanjay''' (born on 15 January 1969, at Allahabad) is an author - a novelist and short-story writer, script writer and documentary film producer. She has been working in the Indian media industry for over two decades. She has written numerous books on various topics. She has even made various documentary and short films for both government agencies and for private companies.
==Early life== Born in Allahabad (Uttar Pradesh), she did her schooling from St. Anthony's School. She did her graduation from Allahabad University in Economics and post graduation in ancient history and culture. After completing her post graduation in mass media studies from Indian Institute Of Mass Communication, she joined the media industry. Her professional career in the field of writing started more than twenty years back in New Delhi.
==Notable work== Her most notable works are Hindi novels Smritiyan and Atank Ke Saaye Mein.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://pib.nic.in/newsite/PrintRelease.aspx?relid=117868 | title=VICE PRESIDENT RELEASES THE BOOK ‘AATANK KE SAAYE MEN’ BY GARIMA SANJAY | work=pib.nic.in | accessdate=26 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.jagranjosh.com/current-affairs/vice-president-released-a-book-titled-smritiyan-authored-by-garima-sanjay-1373715870-1 | title=Vice President Released a Book titled Smritiyan authored by Garima Sanjay | work=jagranjosh.com | accessdate=26 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://164.100.88.150/newsite/erelease.aspx?relid=117868 | title=“Aatank Ke Saaye Men” | work=Press Information Bureau Govt of India | accessdate=27 May 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite book | url=http://www.worldcat.org/title/atanka-ke-saye-mem/oclc/934713346 | title=Atank Ke Saaye Mein | publisher=Naī Dillī : Pratibhā Pratishṭhāna | author=Garima Sanjay | year=2015 | isbn=9789383111664}}</ref> In film industry her highly appreciated works are "GLOF" (Glacial Lake Outburst Flood) for UNDP, "Madan Lal Dhingra" for Films Division of India and "Bhartiya Police- Saahas Yeh Bhi" for BPR&D under the guidance of Dr Kiran Bedi.
