{{distinguish|Ngbaka language}} {{Infobox language |name=Mbaka |nativename= Ngbaka Ma'bo |states=[[Central African Republic|CAR]], [[Republic of Congo]] |ethnicity=[[M'Baka people|M'Baka]] |speakers={{sigfig|201,600|2}} |date=1984–2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam1=[[Ubangian languages|Ubangian]] |fam2=Sere–Mba |fam3=[[Ngbaka languages|Ngbaka]] |fam4=Western |lc1=nbm|ld1=Ngbaka Ma’bo |lc2=gix|ld2=Gilima |glotto=bwak1244 |glottorefname=Bwaka }}
The '''Mbaka''' or '''Bwaka''' language, '''''Ngbaka Ma'bo''''' (also called ''Gbaka, Ma'bo, Ngbwaka, Ngbaka Limba'') is a major [[Ubangian languages|Ubangian language]] spoken by the [[Mbaka people]] of [[Central African Republic|CAR]] and Congo.
It's not clear how distinct the Gilima variety is, or whether it should be considered a separate language.
