{{Infobox language |name=Thai Song |nativename=Lao Song |states=[[Thailand]] |speakers={{sigfig|32300|2}} |date= 2000 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Kradai |fam1=[[Kra–Dai languages|Kra–Dai]] |fam2=[[Tai languages|Tai]] |fam3=[[Southwestern Tai languages|Southwestern]] (Thai) |fam4=Chiang Saen |script=[[Thai script]], [[Tai Viet]] |iso3=soa |glotto=thai1259 |glottorefname=Thai Song }}
'''Thai Song''', or '''Lao Song''', is a [[Tai languages|Tai language]] of [[Thailand]]. The Tai Song originally settled in [[Phetchaburi Province]], and from there went to settle in various provinces such as Kanchanaburi, Ratchaburi, Suphanburi, Nakhon Pathom, Samut Sakhon, Samut Songkhram, Nakhon Sawan, and Phitsanulok (Somsonge 2012).
==Further reading== *[[Marc Miyake|Miyake, Marc]]. 2014. [http://www.amritas.com/141129.htm#11232353 Averaging Thai Song tones].
