The Udege alphabet is currently written in two versions of the Cyrillic alphabet, known respectively as the "Petersburg" and the "Khabarovsk" versions. The Khabarovsk version is used more often<ref name>{{cite book| author = М. Д. Симонов, В. Т. Кялундзюга | chapter = | chapter-url = | format = | url = | title = Словарь удэгейского языка (хорский диалект). Препринт | orig-year = | agency = | edition = |location= |year= 1998 |publisher= |at= |volume= I |issue = | pages = 3-6, 59| page = | series = | isbn = | ref = }}</ref>.
